# HCDE530 Cursor Rules

## Project Directory Structure

Keep this structure section current whenever files or folders are added, renamed, or removed.

```text
hcde530/
├── .cursor/
│   └── rules/
│       ├── project-standards.mdc
│       ├── python-coursework.mdc
│       └── week2-project.mdc
├── HCDE530_week2_project/
│   ├── app_review_word_count.py
│   ├── clean_demo_responses.py
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── demo_responses.csv
│   ├── demo_word_count.py
│   └── week2.md
├── HCDE530_week3_project/
│   ├── week3_analysis_buggy.py
│   ├── week3.md
│   ├── week3_survey_cleaned.csv
│   └── week3_survey_messy.csv
├── HCDE530_week4_project/
│   └── week4_api_category_votes.py
└── README.md
```

## Maintenance Rule

- When making file changes, update the directory structure above in the same task.
- Keep paths accurate and alphabetized within each folder.
- Do not include `.git` internals in the tree.
- Preserve beginner-friendly organization and avoid unnecessary folder churn.
